CONTEXT BoundedMaintenance IN ENGLISH
-- Negative test for the ⊆-containment certificate (§6.5). `markFirst` sets
-- `firstOf` only for an item that is IN a bag and has no predecessor — a subset
-- of the region `clearWhenEmpty` allows (`itemIn~;V`, i.e. bags that have items).
-- So inserts land inside the allow-region and deletes land outside it; `firstOf`
-- converges even though the insert-region and the allow-region are NOT equal,
-- only `⊆`. This is the Sequence first/last-vs-emptiness shape, and it MUST stay
-- silent — equality-based certification alone would (wrongly) flag it.

RELATION itemIn[Item*Bag] [UNI]
RELATION nextIn[Item*Item] [UNI,INJ,IRF]
RELATION firstOf[Bag*Item]

ROLE ExecEngine MAINTAINS markFirst
RULE markFirst : itemIn - (nextIn~;itemIn) |- firstOf~
VIOLATION ( TXT "{EX} InsPair;firstOf;Bag;", TGT I, TXT ";Item;", SRC I )

ROLE ExecEngine MAINTAINS clearWhenEmpty
RULE clearWhenEmpty : firstOf |- itemIn~;V
VIOLATION ( TXT "{EX} DelPair;firstOf;Bag;", SRC I, TXT ";Item;", TGT I )

ENDCONTEXT
